HEADWORD: Kerned
<hw>Kerned</hw> <pr>(k⟦etil⟧rnd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Print.)</fld>
<def>Having part of the face projecting beyond the body or shank; --
said of type.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In Roman, <xex>f</xex> and <xex>j</xex> are
the only <xex>kerned</xex> letters.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>MacKellar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kernel</ent>⟦br⟧
